history.content:
No it will not expand. 

From Head TA on 186 Piazza:

"The course will, unfortunately, not be able to expand any further. We actually expanded from something like 550 to 700 students early on in the enrollment process, and we've only got enough staff, resources, and budget to accommodate 700 students."

--------

Yeah, unfortunately, we won't be expanding to anything more than 700; an online class is only online in terms of lecture timing. Everything else stays the same (discussions, OH, exams, etc), and we sadly just don't have enough staff or resources to support anything more than 700 people (which is already the largest offering we've ever had).

No it will not expand. 

From Head TA on 186 Piazza:

"The course will, unfortunately, not be able to expand any further. We actually expanded from something like 550 to 700 students early on in the enrollment process, and we've only got enough staff, resources, and budget to accommodate 700 students."
Since it’s an online class, is this a possibility?
